{
  "stem": "304.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we looked at each other, and we had to hold on because we were hundreds-- thousands-- of people with strange clothes, without hair, and it was very easy to get lost.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then to find someone in the crowds was impossible.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the three of us are holding onto each other-- mother, Lilly, and I.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so did other sisters and the few mothers who were-- because not too many people had the mothers with them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were just the lucky ones, our age level, that we were together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we were taken, given over to a block alteste, and taken to Camp C.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I remember, at Camp C, they had 30 barracks, a thousand-- about 1,000 people in one barracks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Our barracks was number 20C-- 26.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The block alteste was named Itel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She was one of the cruel, mean peo-- persons I met during my stay in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She was very jealous, and she told us-- she gave us a speech when we arrived-- she said, you were still at home with your parents.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You still had enough food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You were warm, and I was already here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You have a [NON-ENGLISH], you have a-- a [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] leisure place, according what I had when I came to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then she  told us, in the gate you came in-- and she pointed to the chimney-- the chimneys you will go out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And when we turned to the chimneys, it was the first time I realized that those are crematoriums.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And even though I come from a small town in Czechoslovakia, we had a crematorium in our city.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In certain-- in our town.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had a gymnasium, we had a crematorium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So I knew what it is.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
